This repository reproduces the evaluation pipeline, models, and reported results of
the paper "A Leak-Safe Within-User Benchmark for Compact Surface-EMG Grasp Decoding,
with a Causal Sequence-Reasoning Decoder" (Barrett & Hartley, ReAble Labs, 2026).

It is a research reproducibility artifact. It does NOT include, and ReAble Labs does
not release here:

  - trained model weights or checkpoints (results are reproduced by re-running the
    pipeline on public data);
  - any ReAble Labs hardware designs, PCB layouts, schematics, bills of materials,
    firmware, or mechanical/CAD assets;
  - clinical, deployment, or product-integration code;
  - any unpublished models or methods beyond those reported in the paper.

All results are obtained from the publicly available NinaPro DB2 dataset
(http://ninapro.hevs.ch), which is governed by its own license and terms of use.
No human-subjects data were collected for this work.
